{{Audio|file=Old Doll.mp3|align=center|volume=0.225|secrettext=Very scary level indeed!!}}{{Background|file=Level_-121_New_Background.gif}}{{DISPLAYTITLE: <span style="font-family:Fira Code; color:white;">Level 144: "THE GRAVEYARD OF WANDERERS."}}{{Alt Class|ent=5|env=5|ext=4|no=144}}{{Blurimage|file=Level_-121_New.webp|caption=The most infamous picture of '''Level 144'''. Photographer is missing.|align=right}}'''Level 144''', colloquially known as "THE GRAVEYARD OF THE WANDERERS." or "The Anomaly Overload", is the 145th level of [[Backrooms Wiki|the Backrooms]]. It was discovered on June 13th, 2005.

== Description ==
'''Level 144''' is an endless series of unstable rolling hills and lifeless dirt, iron gates and dead trees spread sparsely across, surrounding the many mangled graveyards. The weather is perpetually cloudy, and acidic rain showers fall from the endless cloudscape that envelopes its limitless hills. The air is thick with so many toxins, it becomes difficult to breathe. All that exists on the level becomes glitched and fragmented eventually. Some pieces float mid-air and appear where they shouldn't be.

All resources that '''Level 144''' could ever comprise are dangerous. The most common ones are [[Object 44|Cashew Water]], [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]], and [[Object 7|Devil's Ambrosia]].

Long stays within '''Level 144''' pose many dangers to the body and the mind. The sudden shifts between flashing lights with constant movement and utter stillness cause conditions such as color blindness, myopia, and epilepsy. Other diseases triggered include dementia, Huntington's disease, and migraines. Such conditions result from both the atmosphere and the surface, which retain a wide variety of substances that affect the human mind in unexpected ways.

'''Level 144''' manifests a multitude of other threats; one of the most formidable is "The Divine Curse," cataloged as Phenomenon 70. Upon occurrence, the entire level falls apart, and multiple regions and objects turn harshly disorganized, unstable, and glitched, repeatedly teleporting and breaking. When it ceases a few hours later, the level returns to its original state.{{Blurimage|align=left|file=spooky tornado.webp|caption=A picture of a tornado.}}Another significant peril in '''Level 144''' is colossal, pitch-black, and glitched tornadoes known as "The Hurricane" or "The Tornado." These tornadoes introduce themselves as a dreary mixture of a tornado and a hurricane formed by acid rain, Corruption, strong winds, and glitched objects. Their winds are increasingly strong, pulling even the heaviest of objects effortlessly. Anything that comes into contact with one of these tornadoes will be fragmented, corroded, and infected with Corruption. Otherwise, it might be absorbed into the tornado, expanding its life span. As they travel, tornadoes slowly shed part of their material into the environment, which dissipates into a thick, lethal fog that should not be inhaled.

{{Blurimage|align=right|file=Gravestone.png|caption=A gravestone after being struck by a tornado.}}'''Level 144''' is wholly and deeply infected by an everlasting, dark, highly infective substance only known as Corruption. This substance spreads deep into an item's molecular structure and slowly shreds it apart from the inside. Objects infected with Corruption will become completely stationary, and any chemical reactions they could trigger will cease immediately. Once the vessel is entirely broken apart, a pitch-dark husk of pure Corruption is left behind.

Corruption is predominantly composed of [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]] and a myriad of additional substances present in the many hills of rubble and the thick clouds of acid. The Corruption is believed to form when [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]] lingers far too long in the environment, eventually merging with substances it catches over time.

== Entities ==
Several distinct entities inhabit this level; these include [[Foams]], [[Entity 10|Skin-Stealers]], [[Entity 3|Smilers]], [[Tornadoes]], [[Entity 8|Hounds]], [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]], [[Entity 5|Clumps]], [[The Armless]], etc. Other than these entities, there are two other entities endemic to '''Level 144''':

=== The Ravens ===
{{Entity Class|Agg=1|Int=4|Dan=4|Hab=Level  144|no=UND.}}{{Blurimage|caption=An image of a Raven.|file=Level_-121_Raven.png|align=left}}The Ravens are quite uncommon entities that reside within '''Level 144'''. Ravens resemble what should be an ordinary raven from [[the Frontrooms]]. However, many wanderers who have come across them describe immense discomfort and uneasiness. Strangely enough, none of them can describe what feels so off-putting. These entities are believed to persistently stalk wanderers around the level; they will not stop following them until they die or exit the level.

Ravens are carriers of Corruption, they will drop the infection wherever they go, effectively dooming any area they visit. Wanderers are advised to run from it before the Raven notices their presence.

Ravens seem to have mind-bending properties that never allow wanderers to see them in their genuine aspect, giving them an elusive and glitching presence. This impact also extends to technology. Nearby electronics are driven to malfunction, and video/photographic equipment will suffer the same impacts as wanderers, albeit wildly amplified.

=== Graveplants ===
{{Entity Class|Agg=5|Int=3|Dan=5|Hab=Level 144|no=UND.}}{{Blurimage|align=right|caption=An artist's depiction of a Graveplant.|file=Graveplant.png}}Mortifloria Umbralis, also known as a Graveplant, is an intelligent plant-like entity that can be found in the graveyards. It presents itself as an 8 ft tall carnivorous and venomous plant, like Drosera and Sarracenia, from [[the Frontrooms]]. An ordinary Graveplant retains vines with thorns on its base and three pink structures on its top that saw and digest prey. These structures have a concentrated amount of Corruption that allows for them to digest anything quickly.

To attract prey, it releases a pleasant smell when there are victims nearby. Once the target is close enough, the Graveplant will trap them with its vines and then pull them towards its digestive system. Alternatively, Graveplants may release deadly smoke to kill their victim seamlessly.

== Colonies and Outposts ==
Due to the unfortunate nature of Level 144, the establishment of any communities is not possible. Despite all the attempts to inhabit it, it all resulted in slow, agonizing deaths.

== Entrances and Exits ==

=== Entrances ===

* [[No-Clipping|No-clipping]] in highly unstable levels has a 20% chance to lead here.
* Being killed by a bird at any [[:Category:Anomalous Levels|anomalous]] level.
* Falling through the floor in [[Level 305]].
* Having a stroke or hallucinating in [[Level 16]] may lead here.
* Piercing through [[Level 488]]'s cloudscape may lead one here.
* Being buried alive in [https://backrooms.fandom.com/wiki/Category:Darkness dark levels].
* There are multiple entrances from [[Level 630]] in '''Level 144'''.

=== Exits ===

* [[No-Clipping|No-clipping]] into an affected object after Phenomena 70 has a small chance of leading to [[Level 137]].
* Killing a Raven, or being consumed by the Hurricane will lead to [[the Void]].
* Being corrupted has a 2% chance of leading to [[Level 690]].
* In what is perhaps a more punishing fate, a rare tunnel may lead to [[Level 488]].
* Reach the cloudscape. Find [[Level 385|salvation]].
* Finding a rare tunnel leading underground will take one to [[Level 899]].
* Having a mental meltdown has a 1.7% chance of leading to [[Level 138]].
* <s>The remaining exits are hidden.</s>
